    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at Gradation 1 consistent with MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device with medium model influence. Validation evidence demonstrates RH < 1.0 at all 5 operating points with mean error 8.2%, within MRL 2 acceptance threshold. A screening sensitivity study conducted during model development confirmed low sensitivity of NIH predictions to inlet boundary condition variations, further supporting model adequacy. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision to accept CFD predictions as evidence for worst-case hemolysis operating condition identification.",
